value.value: 基底膜の形態異常

anomaly in the structure, organization and/or placement of the extracellular supportive tissue adjacent to the basal surface of the epithelia, including the epithelium of muscle cells, fat cells and Schwann cells; it is comprised of type IV collagen, laminin, and sulfated proteoglycans and other components and consists of two layers, the basal lamina and the lamina reticularis

definition.value: Note: Basal lamina and lamina reticularis (or of two basal laminae) compose the basement membrane. Thus, in strict sense, the term basement membrane is different from and should not be confused with basal lamina.

value.value: 基底層形態異常

any structural anomaly of the sheet of extracellular matrix characteristically situated under epithelial cells, around muscles, nerves, capillaries, and fat cells, and situated between these elements and the underlying or surrounding connective tissue

definition.value: Note: Basal lamina and lamina reticularis (or of two basal laminae) compose the basement membrane. Thus, in strict sense, the term basement membrane is different from and should not be confused with basal lamina.

value.value: 胚性/胎生の脳室下帯形態異常

any structural anomaly of the transient proliferative population of neurons that expands exponentially during late prenatal development; it is a continuous germinal zone distinct from the ventricular zone that surrounds the brain ventricles
出生後の脳室下帯形態異常

any structural anomaly of the mitotically active layer of cells surrounding the brain ventricles in the adult that consists of migrating neuroblasts, astrocytes and transitory amplifying progenitor cells
淡蒼球原基の形態異常

any structural anomaly of a distinct elevation of a transient proliferating cell mass of the fetal subventricular zone; this mass contributes most of its cells to the neocortex; however, hippocampal neurons, thalamus, septum and olfactory bulb neurons are also partly derived from the MGE
線条体原基の形態異常

any structural anomaly of a distinct elevation of a transient proliferating cell mass of the fetal subventricular zone; this mass contributes most of its cells to the striatum; however, neocortex, thalamus, septum and olfactory bulb neurons are also partly derived from the LGE
尾部神経節隆起の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the caudally located, distinct elevation of a transient proliferating cell mass of the fetal subventricular zone, located adjacent to the lateral ventricle
吻側遊走流の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the transient structure formed by neurons migrating from the subventricular zone into the olfactory bulbs
動眼神経核の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the group of motor neurons in the floor of the midbrain that gives rise to motor fibers of the oculomotor nerve
舌下神経核の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the group of motor neurons throughout most of the length of the medulla oblongata that give rise to the motor fibers of the hypoglossal nerve
下顎後退症

abnormal posterior-shifted positioning of the upper or lower jaw relative to the facial skeleton and soft tissues; a type of malocclusion, that is, misalignment of the teeth caused by abnormal positioning of the jaws; the mandible is more frequently affected than the maxilla
角膜上皮の欠損
absence of the single layer of large flattened cells that cover the surface of the cornea
デスメ膜の形態異常

any structural anomaly in the transparent homogeneous acellular layer found between the substantia propria and the endothelial layer of the cornea, considered to be a highly developed basement membrane
デスメ膜の欠如
absence of the transparent homogeneous acellular layer normally found between the substantia propria and the endothelial layer of the cornea
内耳道の異常

any structural anomaly in the canal beginning at the opening of the internal acoustic meatus in the posterior cranial fossa, passing laterally through the petrous portion of the temporal bone to end at the fundus, where a thin plate of bone separates it from the vestibule; it gives passage to the facial and vestibulocochlear nerves together with the labyrinthine artery and veins
らせん縁の形態異常
any structural anomaly in the border of the spiral lamina, i.e. the thickened periosteum covering the upper plate of the bony spiral lamina of the cochlea
らせん靭帯の形態異常
any structural anomaly in the thickened periosteal lining of the bony cochlea that forms the outer wall of the cochlear duct to which the basal lamina attaches
骨迷路異常

any structural anomaly in the series of cavities (cochlea, vestibule, and semicircular canals) contained within the otic capsule of the petrous portion of the temporal bone; the bony labyrinth is filled with perilymph, in which the delicate, endolymph-filled membranous labyrinth is suspended
アブミ骨底の異常
any structural anomaly in the flat portion of the stapes that fits in the oval window
らせん靭帯線維細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly in the four types of fibrocytes (types I, II , III and IV) that constitute the spiral ligament

value.value: any structural anomaly of type I spiral ligament fibrocytes which occupy the region beneath the stria vascularis

label.value: abnormal type II spiral ligament fibrocytes

value.value: Ⅱ型らせん靭帯線維細胞の異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal type II spiral ligament fibrocytes

value.value: any structural anomaly of type II spiral ligament fibrocytes found in the suprastrial zone and the central area of the spiral ligament beneath the spiral prominence

label.value: abnormal type III spiral ligament fibrocytes

value.value: Ⅲ型らせん靭帯線維細胞の異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal type III spiral ligament fibrocytes

value.value: any structural anomaly of type III spiral ligament fibrocytes which form a cell layer attached to the otic capsule

label.value: abnormal type IV spiral ligament fibrocytes

value.value: Ⅳ型らせん靭帯線維細胞の異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal type IV spiral ligament fibrocytes

value.value: any structural anomaly of type IV spiral ligament fibrocytes found in the triangular space inferior to the basilar crest
固有受容性ニューロンの形態異常
any structural anomaly of the sensory neurons of the dorsal root ganglia that sense body position and send information about how much the muscle is stretched to the spinal cord
前庭神経節の変性

loss of the group of bipolar sensory nerve cell bodies concerned with equilibration that form a swelling on the vestibular part of the eighth cranial nerve in the fundus of the internal acoustic meatus
前庭神経節の欠如

absence of the group of bipolar sensory nerve cell bodies concerned with equilibration that form a swelling on the vestibular part of the eighth cranial nerve in the fundus of the internal acoustic meatus

label.value: abnormal organ of Corti supporting cell morphology

value.value: 支持細胞の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal organ of Corti supporting cell morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly in the highly differentiated epithelial cells with distinctive morphological features surrounding the hair cells in the organ of Corti; inner hair cells (IHCs) are normally surrounded by (inner and outer) phalangeal cells while OHCs are in contact with Deiters and pillar cells; Hensen cells are positioned further laterally in the organ of Corti

label.value: absent organ of Corti supporting cells

value.value: 支持細胞の欠如

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: absent organ of Corti supporting cells

value.value: absence of the highly differentiated epithelial cells with distinctive morphological features that surround all hair cells in the organ of Corti
ダイテルス細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly in the supporting cells of the spiral organ which are attached to the basement membrane and receive the hair cells between their free extremities
ヘンゼン細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly in the supporting cells that form the lateral border of the organ of Corti, immediately to the outer side of Deiters' cells
らせん板縁の欠損
absence of the border of the spiral lamina, i.e. the thickened periosteum covering the upper plate of the bony spiral lamina of the cochlea
ローゼンタール管の形態異常

any structural anomaly in the winding tube of the bony labyrinth that makes two and a half turns about the modiolus of the cochlea; it is divided incompletely into two compartments by a winding shelf of bone, the bony spiral lamina
ローゼンタール管の矮小化
reduced size of the winding tube of the bony labyrinth that makes two and a half turns about the modiolus of the cochlea
ローゼンタール管の欠如
absence of the winding tube of the bony labyrinth that makes two and a half turns about the modiolus of the cochlea
基底膜の異常

any structural anomaly in the membrane extending from the bony spiral membrane to the basilar crest of the cochlea; it forms the greater part of the floor of the cochlear duct separating the latter from the scala tympani, and it supports the organ of Corti
耳胞の欠如
absence of the simple epithelial sac formed from the otic placode that gives rise to the structures of the inner ear
耳胞の矮小化
reduced size of the simple epithelial sac formed from the otic placode that gives rise to the structures of the inner ear
耳胞の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the otic vesicle, typically resulting in decreased size
柱細胞の欠如
absence of the supporting cells that form the inner and outer walls of the tunnel in the organ of Corti
前庭蝸牛神経節の欠如
absence of the group of neuron cell bodies associated with the eighth cranial nerve during embryogenesis; splits in later development to form the cochlear and vestibular ganglia
内耳前庭の欠如
absence of the cavity between the semicircular canals and the cochlea of the inner ear
球形嚢の欠如
absence of the smaller of the two sacs in the vestibule
球形嚢の肥大化
enlarged size of the cavity between the semicircular canals and the cochlea of the inner ear
球形嚢の矮小化
reduced size of the cavity between the semicircular canals and the cochlea of the inner ear
砧骨の欠如
absence of the middle of the three auditory ossicles
槌骨の欠如
absence of the largest of the three auditory ossicles, which resembles a club or hammer
胸骨の開裂
the appearance of an abnormal division in the long flat bone of the chest which articulates with clavicle and first seven rib pairs
胸骨の短縮
reduced length of the long flat bone of the chest which articulates with clavicle and first seven rib pairs
胸骨分節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of one segments of the primordial sternum of the embryo; these segments fuse to form the body of the adult vertebrate sternum
